    "full_draft": "A private terrace at the Lodge at Torrey Pines on a May evening, the ocean out there beyond the pines, and Spanish guitar settling into the air before the first guest even picks up a glass. Choosing live music for something this intimate says something about how much this milestone matters to you.\n\nThe thing that goes wrong with background music at a dinner like this is a guitarist who locks into a volume and a mood at setup and never reads the room again. Cocktail hour sounds the same as the quietest moment between courses. What I do instead is treat the three hours as one long arc, lighter and open during arrivals, present through dinner conversation, warmer and slower as the evening winds down. The music shifts when the room shifts, and no one ever has to ask.\n\nThe Lodge terrace is a space I know. I'm fully self-contained with professional sound calibrated for outdoor flow, and I arrive early enough that everything is dialed before anyone arrives.\n\nSolo Spanish Guitar — $1,200\n3 hours | Professional sound, full setup and breakdown, repertoire shaped to your evening\n\nI can hold May 17th while you finalize the details. Just say the word.\n\nAlex Guillen\n(619) 755-3246",
